<dl id="n36207e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36207e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36207e"> 207(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Leadbeater</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[The Liberal Catholics.]</font> The Liberal Catholic Church freely mixes old-time religion with Theosophy. According to <mark>Charles W. Leadbeater</mark> (Regionary Bishop of Australia) the holy eucharist, for example, is not merely a means of grace for the individual, but also a &ldquo;plan for helping on the evolution of the world by the frequent outpourings of floods of spiritual force&rdquo;. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 285</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
